name: Steve Savicki
textComment: Featured 20 seconds into https://youtu.be/YTXyYNcLiJg for 1985-'84:  Well, awakeness seems to be more popular than closed eyes, but I managed to get some in the chorus.  Eyes can be in any format, but was inspired this time by their ads along with their wear.  Eyewear is mostly glasses, and standard eye ads seem to be makeup.  However, the search extended to movie posters and other types of advertising products.  The record that I’ve seen reflects that the album was started a year before its released.  Therefore, there are images of both ’84 and ’85 here.  Please note that search engines can be inaccurate and images can be mistagged with the wrong year.  Images used were in the order of the search results.  I don’t like to discriminate; I prefer this “mixed bag” approach.  The second song was only more time bought to include more images (nothing lyrical about it at all; theme is the same as the first).
